  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 7033 sitting between the negative gamma pit at 7015 and the massive positive gamma wall at 7050, dealers are currently in buy-the-dip mode after the -4.7% drop, providing support around current levels. The PIN regime with 111B in total GEX creates a strong mean-reversion environment where dealers will aggressively sell any push toward the 7050 gamma wall (11.7B) and buy weakness back toward 7015. Key inflection points are the 7015 negative gamma strike below (where dealer buying accelerates) and the 7000 level which holds another major 9.6B positive gamma wall that should act as strong support.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect bouncy, range-bound trading between 7015-7050 with dealers capping upside.",
